@startuml
title Viaverse Search Index / SEO Page — State Diagram

[*] --> PENDING_INDEX
PENDING_INDEX --> INDEXED_VISIBLE : public + approved
PENDING_INDEX --> INDEXED_HIDDEN : private/not approved
INDEXED_VISIBLE --> STALE_REBUILD_NEEDED : entity updated
STALE_REBUILD_NEEDED --> INDEXED_VISIBLE : rebuilt
INDEXED_VISIBLE --> REMOVED : deleted/suspended
INDEXED_HIDDEN --> INDEXED_VISIBLE : visibility restored
INDEXED_VISIBLE --> SEO_DRAFT : SEO candidate
SEO_DRAFT --> SEO_PUBLISHED : quality ok
SEO_DRAFT --> SEO_NOINDEX : thin/duplicate
SEO_PUBLISHED --> SEO_NOINDEX : quality drop

REMOVED --> [*]

note bottom
Noindex is safer than publishing thin/duplicate/private pages.
Canonical and schema.org metadata belong to SEO projection, not domain entities.
end note
@enduml
